< href="https://hubdockercom/repository/docker/wabayang/jelu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://hubdockercom/repository/docker/wabayang/jelu

this method probably easiest are used

docker provide embeds fetchebookmetada executable automatically import books based their title authors isbn

expects config mounted /config database /database pictures folder /files/images imports dir /files/imports

sample compose would look like that :

version: '33'
services:
 atrule">jeluimage atrule">container_name atrule">volumes ~/jelu/config:/config
 ~/jelu/database:/database
 ~/jelu/files/images:/files/images
 ~/jelu/files/imports:/files/imports
 /etc/timezone:/etc/timezone:ro
 atrule">ports:11111
 atrule">restartstopped

defaults :

default environment variables loaded dockerfile class="languageshell">env assignleft variable">jelu_database_path="/database/"
env variable">jelu_files_images"/files/images/"
env variable">jelu_files_imports"/files/imports/" means said above just need mount /files/images /files/imports /config

arm versions must add variable automatic metadata fetching :
jelu_metadata_calibre_path=/usr/bin/fetchebookmetadata
